  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The bundler does detect them. If we keep the wrapping `if`, it will transpile to something like:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n// ...\r\n{\r\n  // whatever was here on top on the warning\r\n}\r\n// ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith the condition inside the `warning` method, it's completely stripped.\r\n\r\nFYI this is what React is doing for their [`invariant`](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/master/packages/shared/invariant.js) and [`warning`](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/master/packages/shared/warning.js) functions.",
    "created_at": "2018-12-19T15:59:12Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/3367#issuecomment-448646584",
    "id": 448646584,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3367",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQ0ODY0NjU4NA==",
